
// Concatenate the value of [.base], a forward-slash, and the first href attribute found in the current [.dp] node's descendants, using [strings.concat]. The second [get-value] uses an expression to retrieve the first href attribute from the children of the node referenced by [.dp].
strings.concat
   get-value:x:@.base
   .:/
   get-value:x:"@.dp/#/./*/\\@href/[0,1]"
